## How to use this directory

- **Agents** find their open work by running `tayfa-inbox <tag>` (see below). For a manual view, search coordination files for `@<tag>`.
- **Tasks** live in the coordination file for their workstream, not in scratchboards.
- **Memos** live in the stream that owns them. Cross-reference across streams by linking, never duplicate.
- **Scratchboards** under `scratchboards/<agent>/main.md` are personal workspaces — not read by other agents. Sophisticated agents may build their own memory system in their directory (multiple files, subdirs) but the baseline is a single `main.md`.

## Inbox tool

`tayfa-inbox <tag>` lists open tasks, bugs, and unresolved memos
addressed to `@tag`. Always the first thing to run when picking up
session context.

Sample output:

```
$ tayfa-inbox backend
============================================================
  INBOX for @backend
  (/path/to/project/dev/coordination)
============================================================

── OPEN TASKS (3) ──
  webapp.md:50  **Admin project viewer.** ...
  ...

── OPEN BUGS (0) ──
  (none)

── MEMOS ADDRESSED TO YOU (1) ──
  webapp.md:159  <URGENT> Orch poll loop dies after first job

Total open items: 4
```

Filters out change-log entries, registry rows, and resolved items
(struck-through memos, `#tag` acknowledgements).

## Structure

```
dev/coordination/
├── README.md              ← you are here
├── AGENTS.md              ← global agent registry
├── ONBOARDING.md          ← opening ritual for fresh contexts
├── <workstream>.md        ← one per active workstream
└── scratchboards/
    └── <agent>/main.md    ← per-agent private workspace
```

(Two extra dirs — `.presence/` and `.pings/` — exist if you've opted
into the optional ping system. They're gitignored and harmless if
unused.)

## Naming conventions

- `@tag` = agent has active work on an item
- `#tag` = agent has completed their part
- Completed tasks move to the `## Done` / `## Fixed` section with tags flipped
- Resolved memos are struck through with `~~` so agents skip them when scanning
- Coordination files should stay under ~300 lines; housekeep when they exceed

## Adding a new workstream

1. Run `tayfa-add-workstream <name>` (creates `<name>.md` from the template)
2. Add a row to the table above
3. Register any new agents in `AGENTS.md` (`tayfa-add-agent <tag>`)
